        <p> {{ page.overview.intro|raw }} The bus came immediately, we held our cards to the reader and beep, nothing. Again... another beep. Huh? Ok, let's first pay for a simple trip and then we'll see. While sitting, we pondered what wasn't right. That was always included, wasn't it? What had we always booked?!? </p>
        <p> Well, in the Kleinwalsertal we wanted to change buses and beep again. And then it clicked with us. We still had to book the bus ticket separately because we were staying on the German side. In the Kleinwalsertal, the ticket is integrated into the spa card. We had somehow managed to suppress this knowledge, so instead of our planned route, we headed to the Walserhaus to book the tickets there. Instead of walking the 2.5 kilometers along the road, we walked along the Breitach and enjoyed the pleasant air right by the water. When we arrived at the Walserhaus, we booked the tickets for the next few days after some discussion, and decided to take a ride on the Heuberg chairlift. On the way down, a very fresh wind picked up and the first thick clouds came into view. So we ended up in the adjacent caf√© for lunch. Meanwhile, the weather was getting worse and the weather app was talking about thunderstorms. Hm ok, we were wearing light clothes and it was getting too cold for us. So we quickly went to the supermarket and then the journey back to Oberstdorf, with valid bus tickets. </p>

