        <p> Then we quickly checked the car rental and arranged a rental car for the weekend. This time we want to drive out a bit and explore other areas. After the paperwork was done there, we went back to the campsite and made ourselves comfortable. </p>
        <p> The clouds mostly moved on without rain and thunderstorms, so we went for another round at the Iller jump. Then there was delicious grilled food until we had to move into the car because it started to pour again. </p>
        <p> At 10 PM it finally stopped raining enough that I went to take a shower. As it later turned out, that was a bad idea! Because this evening ended at the police station in Oberstdorf. Back in the motorhome, I was only able to fall asleep around 4 AM. </p>
        <p> Why? </p>
        <p> Because some goddamned asshole went into the shower cubicle next to me and kept pointing his cell phone under the cabin in my direction. So I went to get my phone, called the cops, and waited. To make a long story short: The night ended at the police station for questioning and in a very troubled night, since of course my mind couldn't switch off. </p>
